/**
 * \page BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest Multiple Choice Test
__________________________________________________________________

Detailed description
__________________________________________________________________

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Description|
This box can be used with a P300 based paradigm to establish a P300 Quiz application. 
The visualisation consists in a question and many possible answer like a multi-choice test.

First, the application let you few seconds to read and to choose an answer. 
When the countdown is finished, all answers are flashed sequentially many times, 
resulting in an evoked potential in the user's brain activity.
This evoked potential can be detected and used to find which answer the user was focused on. 
When the answer is chosen, two button are flashed sequentially, Validate and Retry, 
The button is focused on by the user can be detected with evoked potential too. 
This button permits to load the next question or to change the answer for the current question.

All questions and answers are configured in a XML file.

\image html Doc_BoxAlgorithm_Quiz_Snapshot.png "The Quiz Visualisation" 
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Description|
__________________________________________________________________

Inputs description
__________________________________________________________________

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Inputs|
This box has five inputs. They are all mandatory.
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Inputs|

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Input1|
This input is used for sequencing flashes of answer part. It uses specific stimulation to know which answer should be flashed
(see \ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Setting_4). 
The flash is switched off thanks to the \c OVTK_StimulationId_VisualStimulationStop stimulation
(this is automatically triggered by the \ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_P300IdentifierStimulator box).
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Input1|

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Input2|
This input is used for sequencing flashes of validate part. 
It uses specific stimulation to know which validate or retry button should be flashed
(see \ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Setting_5). 
The flash is switched off thanks to the \c OVTK_StimulationId_VisualStimulationStop stimulation
(this is automatically triggered by the \ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_P300IdentifierStimulator box).
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Input2|

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Input3|
This input is used in order to define the selected answer. See
\ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_P300SpellerVisualisation_Setting_4 to know what stimulation should be used.
The selected answer will be highlighted with a specific color 
(see \ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Setting_23) so the user quickly notices
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Input3|

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Input4|
This input is used in order to define the  validate or retry button selected. See
\ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_P300SpellerVisualisation_Setting_5 to know what stimulation should be used.
The selected button will be highlighted with a specific color 
(see \ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Setting_23) so the user quickly notices
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Input4|

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Input5|
This input is used to display the time remaining before the next step. 
The countdown is managed by specific stimulation (see \ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Setting_6). 
* |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Input5|
__________________________________________________________________

Outputs description
__________________________________________________________________

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Outputs|
 * |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Outputs|

 * |OVP_DocBegin_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Output1|
 This output is used to indicate if the stimulation received correspond to an existing answer or to the validate button, 
 according to the step. This output used two types of stimulations define by 
 \ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Setting_7 and \ref Doc_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Setting_8.  
* |OVP_DocEnd_BoxAlgorithm_MultipleChoiceTest_Output1|
